headline: HIG Q3 Deep Dive: Pricing, Technology Investments, and Competitive Pressures Shape Outlook
summary: Insurance and financial services company The Hartford (NYSE:HIG) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 7.1% year on year to $7.23 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.78 per share was 17.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
